<section id="Box10">
<h2>Day 10 DWC: 2017-04-10 Monday</h2>
</section>

<h3>Reconnecting with nature</h3>



<h5>Sentience, Old Brain, New Brain</h5>

<p>Hidden beneath a screen of dialogue the old brain lurks defensively. It is our very own nature and the place we need to connect with. It is sensory and non-verbal, attracted or repelled. It knows best what we need , sending signals of hunger,thirst, heat, cold pleasure, pain, body function and emotion. To trust and to cherish the essence of life force, is vital.<br />
The new brain learns to speak and read, tell stories solve puzzles. It is curious and likes to learn. Sensory input is labelled and categorised, explained intelligently. Considered and shared.</p>

<h3>Wrangler</h3>

<h5>Horseman and stock keeper</h5>

<p>Herded, coaxed, coerced, persuaded, prodded, bribed. Managed, taught a lesson, punished. Believe in stories. True Stories. Facts. Reading to some purpose. A recipe - for disaster? An algorithm, a DIY manual. How to do this, that or the other thing. Read a leaflet, search the library. Google it, Wikipedia knows everything. No actually there&#39;s more to know. Code.<br />
The stock market, stock photos, stock keeper, take stock, stock pot. Stockman wrangling. Our language is suffused with concepts of conquest and domination.</p>

<h3>Insight</h3>

<h5>Different kinds of mindfulness</h5>

<p>Mindfulness can help connect with nature but as with anything the new brain gets hold of it depends on the stories it tells itself. Making strong connections with the old brain, the source of sensory wisdom, restores full awareness of being part of nature. Meanwhile the cultured new brain disconnects, resists, objects. Follows instructions.<br />
<br />
Vision can make it blind. Thinking and searching for stories or engaging explanations. Plots and schemes and plans, twist and spin. Maintaining inner voice, imagine conversations and procedures.<br />
New brain works out. Predicts activities and outcomes. Mental habits, thoughts, imaginings play like film across a screen of consciousness.<br />
<br />
Mindfulness needs to be in nature, a relaxation into trusting that we are part of it.<br />
<br />
Reconnecting with nature is to recognise it.</p>

<p><br />
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=juEqplbnh3Q">... Say it in Broken English</a></p>



